1
00:00:48,421 --> 00:00:50,116
- Merry Christmas.
- Yeah.

2
00:00:50,222 --> 00:00:53,146
I'm glad I run into you.
I wanna talk to you.

3
00:00:53,259 --> 00:00:55,056
I haven't got time.

4
00:00:55,161 --> 00:00:57,925
Oh, make time, consigliere.
Get in the car.

5
00:01:00,032 --> 00:01:01,522
What are you worried about?

6
00:01:01,634 --> 00:01:03,829
If I wanted to kill you,
you'd be dead already.

7
00:01:04,937 --> 00:01:06,097
Get in.

8
00:01:18,617 --> 00:01:20,710
- I'm gonna buy some fruit.
- Okay, Pa.

9
00:01:27,259 --> 00:01:29,056
Hi. Merry Christmas.

10
00:01:29,161 --> 00:01:31,117
I want some fruit over there.

11
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:36,061
Gimme three of them.

12
00:01:38,003 --> 00:01:39,231
No, that one.

13
00:01:58,624 --> 00:02:00,285
Fredo!

14
00:02:47,773 --> 00:02:48,762
Papa.

15
00:02:50,309 --> 00:02:51,401
Papa!

16
00:02:57,650 --> 00:03:00,414
Would you like me better
if I were a nun...

17
00:03:00,519 --> 00:03:02,475
like in the story, you know?

18
00:03:06,358 --> 00:03:09,247
Then would you like me better
if I were Ingrid Bergman?

19
00:03:09,361 --> 00:03:10,988
Now that's a thought.

20
00:03:14,934 --> 00:03:18,165
No, I would not like you better
if you were Ingrid Bergman.

21
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:20,101
- Mike-
- What's the matter?

22
00:03:36,555 --> 00:03:38,511
They don't say
if he's dead or alive.

23
00:04:01,447 --> 00:04:04,575
- Sonny, Michael.
- Michael, where you been?

24
00:04:04,683 --> 00:04:06,241
Is he all right?

25
00:04:06,352 --> 00:04:09,082
We don't know yet.
There's all kinds of stories.

26
00:04:10,623 --> 00:04:12,022
He was hit bad, Mikey.

27
00:04:13,559 --> 00:04:16,687
- Are you there?
- Yeah, I'm here.

28
00:04:16,795 --> 00:04:19,127
Where you been?
I was worried.

29
00:04:19,231 --> 00:04:21,290
Didn't Tom tell you?
I called.

30
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:25,131
No. Look, come home, kid.
You should be with Mama, you hear?

31
00:04:25,237 --> 00:04:26,192
All right.

32
00:04:33,445 --> 00:04:34,742
Oh, my God.

33
00:04:49,929 --> 00:04:52,420
Go. Who is it?

34
00:04:52,531 --> 00:04:53,930
Open up. It's Clemenza.

35
00:04:56,035 --> 00:04:56,990
What?

36
00:04:57,102 --> 00:04:59,058
There's more news
about your old man.

37
00:05:00,072 --> 00:05:02,028
The word is out on the street
he's already dead.

38
00:05:02,141 --> 00:05:04,029
Shut your mouth.
What's the matter with you?

39
00:05:04,143 --> 00:05:06,566
Jesus Christ!
Take it easy.

40
00:05:06,679 --> 00:05:08,772
- Where was Paulie?
- Paulie was out sick.

41
00:05:08,881 --> 00:05:11,372
- He's been sick all winter.
- How many times he been sick?

42
00:05:11,450 --> 00:05:12,940
Only maybe three, four times.

43
00:05:13,018 --> 00:05:14,974
I asked Freddy if he wants
a different bodyguard.

44
00:05:15,087 --> 00:05:16,714
- He said no.
- Pick him up now.

45
00:05:16,822 --> 00:05:18,551
I don't care how sick he is.

46
00:05:18,657 --> 00:05:21,319
If he's breathin', I want you to
bring him to my father's house now.

47
00:05:21,427 --> 00:05:24,225
- You want me to send people here?
- No, just you and him. Go ahead.

48
00:05:24,330 --> 00:05:25,354
All right.

49
00:05:33,839 --> 00:05:36,171
I'm havin' a couple of our people
come to the house.

50
00:05:40,646 --> 00:05:42,807
- Hello?
- Santino Corleone?

51
00:05:42,915 --> 00:05:44,974
- Yeah.
- We have Tom Hagen.

52
00:05:46,085 --> 00:05:49,509
In about three hours, he'll be
released with our proposition.

53
00:05:49,622 --> 00:05:52,978
Listen to everything he has
to say before you do anything.

54
00:05:53,092 --> 00:05:54,616
What's done is done.

55
00:05:54,727 --> 00:05:57,685
And don't lose that famous temper
of yours, huh, Sonny?

56
00:05:57,796 --> 00:05:59,058
No, I'll wait.

57
00:06:13,812 --> 00:06:15,211
Your boss is dead.

58
00:06:18,651 --> 00:06:21,017
I know you're not in
the muscle end of the family...

59
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,008
so I don't want you
to be scared.

60
00:06:24,189 --> 00:06:26,714
I want you
to help the Corleones...

61
00:06:26,825 --> 00:06:28,781
and I want you to help me.

62
00:06:31,897 --> 00:06:33,626
We got him outside his office...

63
00:06:33,732 --> 00:06:35,688
about an hour after
we picked you up.

64
00:06:38,070 --> 00:06:39,298
Drink it.

65
00:06:43,709 --> 00:06:47,133
So now it's up to you to make
the peace between me and Sonny.

66
00:06:51,684 --> 00:06:53,640
Sonny was hot
for my deal, wasn't he?

67
00:06:55,587 --> 00:06:57,543
And you knew it was
the right thing to do.

68
00:06:59,925 --> 00:07:01,984
Sonny will come after you
with everything he's got.

69
00:07:03,195 --> 00:07:05,220
That'll be
his first reaction, sure.

70
00:07:06,465 --> 00:07:08,763
That's why you gotta
talk some sense into him.

71
00:07:08,867 --> 00:07:12,098
The Tattaglia family is behind me
with all their people.

72
00:07:13,072 --> 00:07:15,131
The other New York families
will go along with anything...

73
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:17,128
that will prevent
a full-scale war.

74
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:20,574
Let's face it,
in all due respect...

75
00:07:20,679 --> 00:07:23,239
the Don, rest in peace,
was slippin'.

76
00:07:26,151 --> 00:07:28,107
Ten years ago,
could I have gotten to him?

77
00:07:33,125 --> 00:07:34,615
Well, now he's dead.

78
00:07:34,693 --> 00:07:36,718
He's dead,
and nothing can bring him back.

79
00:07:38,831 --> 00:07:40,856
So you gotta talk to Sonny.

80
00:07:40,966 --> 00:07:42,797
You gotta talk
to the caporegimes-

81
00:07:42,901 --> 00:07:44,857
that Tessio,
that fat Clemenza.

82
00:07:49,808 --> 00:07:51,105
It's good business, Tom.

83
00:07:53,245 --> 00:07:54,371
I'll try.

84
00:07:55,547 --> 00:07:58,209
But even Sonny won't be able
to call off Luca Brasi.

85
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:02,847
Yeah. Well-

86
00:08:04,523 --> 00:08:06,411
Let me worry about Luca.

87
00:08:12,431 --> 00:08:14,228
You just talk to Sonny.

88
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:16,289
And the other two kids.

89
00:08:20,072 --> 00:08:21,471
I'll do my best.

90
00:08:21,573 --> 00:08:22,733
Good.

91
00:08:24,877 --> 00:08:27,368
Now, you can go.

92
00:08:34,253 --> 00:08:37,586
I don't like violence, Tom.
I'm a businessman.

93
00:08:39,124 --> 00:08:41,080
Blood is a big expense.

94
00:09:02,714 --> 00:09:04,511
He's still alive.

95
00:09:04,616 --> 00:09:07,005
They hit him with five shots,
and he's still alive!

96
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:10,508
Well, that's bad luck for me...

97
00:09:10,622 --> 00:09:13,011
and bad luck for you
if you don't make that deal.

98
00:09:58,103 --> 00:10:00,059
Your mother's over
in the hospital with your father.

99
00:10:00,172 --> 00:10:02,128
Looks like he's gonna
pull through, thank God.

100
00:10:04,743 --> 00:10:06,904
- That's a lot of bad blood.
- What do you think?

101
00:10:07,012 --> 00:10:09,867
It's too far.
I think it's too personal.

102
00:10:09,982 --> 00:10:12,644
- The Don will consider this over.
- You gonna kill all those guys?

103
00:10:12,751 --> 00:10:15,140
- Stay out of it, Mickey.
- Sollozzo's the key.

104
00:10:15,254 --> 00:10:17,449
You get rid of him,
everything falls into line.

105
00:10:17,556 --> 00:10:20,150
What about Luca? Sollozzo
didn't seem worried about Luca.

106
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:25,626
I don't know. If Luca sold out,
we're in a lot of trouble.

107
00:10:25,731 --> 00:10:27,687
Has anyone been able
to get in touch with Luca?

108
00:10:27,799 --> 00:10:29,790
We've been tryin' all night.
He might be shacked up.

109
00:10:29,902 --> 00:10:30,857
Mick, try him again.

110
00:10:30,969 --> 00:10:32,527
Luca never sleeps over
with a broad.

111
00:10:32,638 --> 00:10:34,265
He always goes home
when he's through.

112
00:10:35,674 --> 00:10:38,632
Well, Tom, you're consigliere.

113
00:10:38,744 --> 00:10:41,872
What do we do
if the old man dies, God forbid?

114
00:10:41,980 --> 00:10:43,868
If we lose the old man...

115
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:48,174
we lose our political contacts
and half our strength.

116
00:10:48,287 --> 00:10:51,176
The other New York families might
wind up supporting Sollozzo...

117
00:10:51,290 --> 00:10:53,554
just to avoid
a long destructive war.

118
00:10:53,659 --> 00:10:57,390
This is almost 1946.
Nobody wants bloodshed anymore.

119
00:10:58,630 --> 00:11:00,154
If your father dies...

120
00:11:02,467 --> 00:11:04,128
you'll make the deal, Sonny.

121
00:11:04,236 --> 00:11:06,796
That's easy for you to say.
He's not your father.

122
00:11:06,905 --> 00:11:09,032
I was as much a son to him
as you or Mike.

123
00:11:13,845 --> 00:11:15,073
What is it?

124
00:11:16,348 --> 00:11:18,714
Hey, Paulie, I thought
I told you to stay put.

125
00:11:18,817 --> 00:11:21,445
The guy at the gates,
they say they got a package.

126
00:11:21,553 --> 00:11:23,544
Yeah?
Tessio, go see what it is.

127
00:11:27,426 --> 00:11:29,314
- You want me to hang around?
- Yeah, hang around.

128
00:11:29,428 --> 00:11:30,827
- You all right?
- I'm fine.

129
00:11:30,929 --> 00:11:33,625
Yeah? There's some food
in the icebox. You hungry?

130
00:11:33,732 --> 00:11:35,688
- No, it's all right. Thanks.
- How 'bout a little brandy?

131
00:11:35,801 --> 00:11:37,462
- That's good to sweat it out.
- Sure.

132
00:11:37,569 --> 00:11:39,525
- Go ahead.
- That might be a good idea.

133
00:11:41,773 --> 00:11:44,196
I want you to take care
of that son of a bitch right away.

134
00:11:44,309 --> 00:11:46,834
Paulie sold out the old man.

135
00:11:46,945 --> 00:11:50,039
I don't wanna see him again.
Make that first thing on your list.

136
00:11:50,148 --> 00:11:51,376
Understood.

137
00:11:51,483 --> 00:11:53,713
Hey, Mickey, tomorrow
you get a couple of guys.

138
00:11:53,819 --> 00:11:55,912
Go to Luca's apartment.
Wait for him to show up.

139
00:11:56,021 --> 00:12:00,082
Maybe we shouldn't get Mike
mixed up in this too directly.

140
00:12:00,192 --> 00:12:01,352
Yeah.

141
00:12:02,461 --> 00:12:05,988
Listen, hang around the house
on the phone. It'll be a big help.

142
00:12:07,099 --> 00:12:08,930
Try Luca again. Go ahead.

143
00:12:17,943 --> 00:12:20,776
- What the hell is this?
- It's a Sicilian message.

144
00:12:20,879 --> 00:12:23,370
It means Luca Brasi
sleeps with the fishes.

145
00:12:37,162 --> 00:12:39,585
- I'm goin' now.
- What time you gonna be home?

146
00:12:39,698 --> 00:12:41,256
I don't know. Probably late.

147
00:12:43,468 --> 00:12:46,995
- Don't forget the cannoli.
- Yeah, yeah.

148
00:12:49,708 --> 00:12:53,496
Rocco, sit on the other side.
You block the rearview mirror.

149
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:57,170
Sonny's runnin' wild.

150
00:12:57,249 --> 00:12:59,205
He's thinkin' of goin'
to the mattresses already.

151
00:12:59,317 --> 00:13:01,877
We gotta find a spot
over on the West Side.

152
00:13:01,987 --> 00:13:05,081
We'll try
309 West 43rd Street.

153
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:07,454
You know any good spots
on the West Side?

154
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:09,982
- Yeah, I'll think about it.
- Think while you're drivin'.

155
00:13:10,095 --> 00:13:12,325
I wanna hit New York
sometime this month.

156
00:13:12,431 --> 00:13:14,387
And watch out for the kids
when you're backin' out.

157
00:13:25,310 --> 00:13:27,642
Paulie, I want you to go
down 39th Street. Colosanto's.

158
00:13:27,746 --> 00:13:30,806
Pick up 18 mattresses for the guys
to sleep. Bring me the bill.

159
00:13:30,916 --> 00:13:33,805
- Yeah, all right.
- Make sure they're clean.

160
00:13:33,919 --> 00:13:37,116
Those guys are gonna be stuck up
in there for a long time.

161
00:13:37,222 --> 00:13:39,315
They're clean. They told me
they exterminate them.

162
00:13:39,424 --> 00:13:41,415
"Exterminate"?
That's a bad word to use.

163
00:13:41,526 --> 00:13:44,484
Exterminate. Get this guy.
See how we don't exterminate you.

164
00:13:44,596 --> 00:13:46,552
- Youse funny, or what?
- Hey, Paulie?

165
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:50,791
- Yeah, Rocco, what'd you do?
- No, me. It wasn't me.

166
00:13:50,869 --> 00:13:52,825
- It's gotta be him.
- Pull over.

167
00:13:52,938 --> 00:13:54,826
I gotta take a leak.

168
00:14:36,648 --> 00:14:38,343
Leave the gun.

169
00:14:38,450 --> 00:14:39,849
Take the cannoli.

170
00:15:02,741 --> 00:15:04,663
- Yeah?
- You're wanted on the telephone.

171
00:15:10,949 --> 00:15:12,940
- Who is it?
- It's some girl.

172
00:15:17,522 --> 00:15:18,614
Hello, Kay?

173
00:15:18,723 --> 00:15:19,985
How's your father?

174
00:15:20,091 --> 00:15:21,786
He's good.
He's gonna make it.

175
00:15:21,893 --> 00:15:23,383
I love you.

176
00:15:25,697 --> 00:15:27,130
I love you!

177
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:30,631
- Michael?
- Yeah, I know.

178
00:15:30,735 --> 00:15:32,532
Tell me you love me.

179
00:15:32,637 --> 00:15:35,003
- I can't talk.
- Can’t you say it?

180
00:15:36,942 --> 00:15:38,705
Yeah, I'll see you tonight.

181
00:15:39,644 --> 00:15:42,636
Why don't you tell
that nice girl you love her?

182
00:15:42,747 --> 00:15:44,703
I love you
with all o' my heart!

183
00:15:44,816 --> 00:15:47,341
If I don't see you again a-soon,
I'm-a gonna die!

184
00:15:48,587 --> 00:15:50,475
Come over here, kid.
Learn somethin'.

185
00:15:50,589 --> 00:15:52,716
You might have to cook
for 20 guys someday.

186
00:15:53,592 --> 00:15:55,822
You see? You start out
with a little bit of oil.

187
00:15:55,927 --> 00:15:57,417
Then you fry some garlic.

188
00:15:57,495 --> 00:16:00,123
Then you throw in some tomatoes,
some tomato paste.

189
00:16:00,232 --> 00:16:02,894
You fry it.
You make sure it doesn't stick.

190
00:16:03,001 --> 00:16:06,164
When you got it to a boil, shove in
all your sausage and meatballs.

191
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:10,598
And a little bit of wine.

192
00:16:14,379 --> 00:16:17,268
And a little bit of sugar.

193
00:16:18,049 --> 00:16:19,937
- And that's my trick.
- Why don't you cut the crap?

194
00:16:20,051 --> 00:16:22,110
I got more important things
for you to do.

195
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:24,814
- How's Paulie?
- Won't see him no more.

196
00:16:26,891 --> 00:16:29,280
- Where you going?
- To the city.

197
00:16:29,394 --> 00:16:30,952
Send some bodyguards with him.

198
00:16:31,062 --> 00:16:32,950
- I'm just going to see Pop.
- Send somebody with him.

199
00:16:33,064 --> 00:16:35,953
He'll be all right.
Sollozzo knows he's a civilian.

200
00:16:36,067 --> 00:16:38,456
- All right. Be careful, huh?
- Yes, sir.

201
00:16:41,573 --> 00:16:43,871
Send somebody with him anyway.

202
00:17:12,270 --> 00:17:13,999
I have to go.

203
00:17:14,105 --> 00:17:15,504
Can I go with you?

204
00:17:16,941 --> 00:17:19,501
No, Kay. There's gonna be
detectives there.

205
00:17:19,611 --> 00:17:21,499
People from the press.

206
00:17:21,613 --> 00:17:23,342
I'll ride in a cab.

207
00:17:26,117 --> 00:17:28,347
I don't want you
to get involved.

208
00:17:31,289 --> 00:17:33,018
When will I see you again?

209
00:17:39,964 --> 00:17:41,852
Go back to New Hampshire...

210
00:17:41,966 --> 00:17:44,093
and I'll call you
at your parents' house.

211
00:17:45,804 --> 00:17:47,863
When will I see you again,
Michael?

212
00:17:49,808 --> 00:17:51,207
I don't know.

213
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:04,365
What are you doing here?

214
00:20:04,476 --> 00:20:06,467
You're not supposed
to be here now.

215
00:20:06,578 --> 00:20:10,139
I'm Michael Corleone.
This is my father.

216
00:20:10,248 --> 00:20:12,808
There's nobody here.
What happened to the guards?

217
00:20:12,917 --> 00:20:15,147
Your father just had
too many visitors.

218
00:20:15,253 --> 00:20:18,142
They interfered
with hospital service.

219
00:20:18,256 --> 00:20:21,145
The police made them leave
about ten minutes ago.

220
00:20:26,097 --> 00:20:29,988
Get me Long Beach 4-5-6-2-0,
please.

221
00:20:32,604 --> 00:20:34,993
Nurse, wait a minute.
Stay here.

222
00:20:38,943 --> 00:20:41,173
Sonny, Michael.
I'm at the hospital.

223
00:20:41,279 --> 00:20:43,839
Listen. I got here late.
There's nobody here.

224
00:20:43,948 --> 00:20:46,940
Nobody. No Tessio's men,
no detectives, nobody.

225
00:20:47,051 --> 00:20:49,849
- Pop is all alone.
- Don't panic. We'll send somebody.

226
00:20:49,954 --> 00:20:52,184
I won't panic.

227
00:20:52,290 --> 00:20:54,850
I'm sorry, but you will
have to leave.

228
00:20:57,795 --> 00:21:00,525
You and I are gonna move my father
to another room.

229
00:21:00,632 --> 00:21:03,692
Can you disconnect those tubes
so we can move the bed out?

230
00:21:03,801 --> 00:21:07,293
- That's out of the question.
- Do you know my father?

231
00:21:07,405 --> 00:21:09,498
Men are coming here
to kill him.

232
00:21:09,607 --> 00:21:11,632
You understand?

233
00:21:11,743 --> 00:21:13,802
Now, help me, please.

234
00:22:30,588 --> 00:22:35,321
- Who are you?
- I am Enzo- the baker.

235
00:22:35,426 --> 00:22:36,825
- You remember me?
- Enzo?

236
00:22:36,928 --> 00:22:38,657
- Yes, Enzo.
- You better get out of here, Enzo.

237
00:22:38,763 --> 00:22:40,651
There's gonna be trouble.

238
00:22:40,765 --> 00:22:43,154
If there is trouble,
I stay here to help you-

239
00:22:43,267 --> 00:22:45,326
For your father.

240
00:22:46,771 --> 00:22:48,500
All right, listen.

241
00:22:48,606 --> 00:22:50,665
Wait for me outside,
in front of the hospital.

242
00:22:50,775 --> 00:22:53,801
