on this son of a bitch.

287
00:28:19,270 --> 00:28:21,500
Craps out last night,
he wants a meeting today.

288
00:28:21,605 --> 00:28:23,334
- What'd he say?
- What did he say?

289
00:28:24,775 --> 00:28:26,834
He wants us to send Michael
to hear the proposition.

290
00:28:26,944 --> 00:28:30,004
And the promise is that the deal
is so good that we can't refuse.

291
00:28:30,614 --> 00:28:32,172
What about Bruno Tattaglia?

292
00:28:32,283 --> 00:28:33,841
That's part of the deal.

293
00:28:33,951 --> 00:28:35,839
Bruno cancels out what they did
to my father.

294
00:28:35,953 --> 00:28:37,841
Sonny, we ought to hear
what they have to say.

295
00:28:39,290 --> 00:28:41,178
No more.
Not this time, Consigliere.

296
00:28:41,292 --> 00:28:44,853
No more meetings, no discussions,
no more Sollozzo tricks.

297
00:28:44,962 --> 00:28:46,691
You give them one message-
I want Sollozzo.

298
00:28:46,797 --> 00:28:48,355
If not, it's all-out war.
We go to the mattresses.

299
00:28:48,466 --> 00:28:50,024
Some of the other families
won't sit still for a war.

300
00:28:50,134 --> 00:28:52,193
- Then they hand me Sollozzo.
- Your father wouldn't like this.

301
00:28:52,303 --> 00:28:55,363
- This is business, not personal.
- They shot my father.

302
00:28:55,473 --> 00:28:58,863
Even shooting your father
was business, not personal, Sonny.

303
00:28:58,976 --> 00:29:00,705
Well, then business
will have to suffer.

304
00:29:00,811 --> 00:29:02,540
And do me a favor, Tom-

305
00:29:02,646 --> 00:29:04,534
No more advice on how
to patch things up.

306
00:29:04,648 --> 00:29:06,479
Just help me win, please.
All right?

307
00:29:13,090 --> 00:29:15,650
I found out about this McCluskey
who broke Mike's jaw.

308
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:17,159
What about him?

309
00:29:17,261 --> 00:29:20,321
He's definitely on Sollozzo's
payroll, and for big money.

310
00:29:20,431 --> 00:29:23,320
McCluskey has agreed
to be the Turk's bodyguard.

311
00:29:23,434 --> 00:29:25,322
What you have to understand,
Sonny...

312
00:29:25,436 --> 00:29:27,495
is that while Sollozzo's
being guarded like this...

313
00:29:27,605 --> 00:29:29,334
he is invulnerable.

314
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:33,001
Nobody has ever gunned down
a New York police captain. Never.

315
00:29:33,110 --> 00:29:36,170
It would be disastrous. All the
five families would come after you.

316
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:39,010
The Corleone family
would be outcast.

317
00:29:39,116 --> 00:29:42,813
Even the old man's political
protection would run for cover.

318
00:29:44,288 --> 00:29:46,347
So do me a favor.

319
00:29:46,457 --> 00:29:49,085
Take this into consideration.

320
00:29:51,896 --> 00:29:53,386
All right, we'll wait.

321
00:29:59,136 --> 00:30:00,535
We can't wait.

322
00:30:01,639 --> 00:30:03,527
Can't wait.

323
00:30:03,641 --> 00:30:05,302
I don't care what Sollozzo says
about a deal.

324
00:30:05,409 --> 00:30:07,468
He's gonna kill Pop.
That's it.

325
00:30:07,578 --> 00:30:09,307
That's the key for him.

326
00:30:09,413 --> 00:30:11,301
Got to get Sollozzo.

327
00:30:11,415 --> 00:30:13,474
Mike is right.

328
00:30:13,584 --> 00:30:15,472
Let me ask you something first.

329
00:30:15,586 --> 00:30:18,646
What about this McCluskey?

330
00:30:18,756 --> 00:30:20,644
What do we do
with this cop?

331
00:30:25,596 --> 00:30:27,655
They want to have a meeting
with me, right?

332
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:32,160
It will be me...

333
00:30:32,269 --> 00:30:34,157
McCluskey and Sollozzo.

334
00:30:35,773 --> 00:30:37,172
Let's set the meeting.

335
00:30:39,944 --> 00:30:43,334
Get our informers to find out
where it's going to be held.

336
00:30:45,449 --> 00:30:49,180
We insist it's a public place-
a bar, a restaurant.

337
00:30:49,286 --> 00:30:53,017
Someplace where there's people,
so I feel safe.

338
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:58,849
They're gonna search me
when I first meet them, right?

339
00:30:58,963 --> 00:31:00,851
So I can't have a weapon
on me then.

340
00:31:04,635 --> 00:31:07,126
But if Clemenza can figure a way...

341
00:31:07,238 --> 00:31:09,627
to have a weapon
planted there for me...

342
00:31:14,578 --> 00:31:16,136
then I'll kill them both.

343
00:31:28,959 --> 00:31:31,484
What are you gonna do?
Nice college boy, huh?

344
00:31:31,595 --> 00:31:33,483
Didn't want to get mixed up
in the family business.

345
00:31:33,597 --> 00:31:35,485
Now you want to gun down
a police captain?

346
00:31:35,599 --> 00:31:37,487
Why? 'Cause he slapped you
in the face a little bit?

347
00:31:37,601 --> 00:31:39,831
Do you think this is the army,
where you shoot them a mile away?

348
00:31:39,937 --> 00:31:41,495
You gotta get up close,
like this and-

349
00:31:41,605 --> 00:31:44,995
You blow their brains all over your
nice Ivy League suit. Come here.

350
00:31:45,109 --> 00:31:47,339
You're taking this
very personal.

351
00:31:47,444 --> 00:31:50,675
Tom, this is business, and this man
is taking it very, very personal.

352
00:31:50,781 --> 00:31:52,703
Where does it say
you can't kill a cop?

353
00:31:52,816 --> 00:31:55,341
- Come on, Mikey.
- Tom, wait a minute.

354
00:31:55,452 --> 00:31:58,182
I'm talking about a cop
that's mixed up in drugs.

355
00:31:58,289 --> 00:32:02,419
I'm talking about a dishonest cop,
a crooked cop...

356
00:32:02,526 --> 00:32:05,381
who got mixed up in the rackets
and got what was coming to him.

357
00:32:05,496 --> 00:32:07,452
That's a terrific story.

358
00:32:07,565 --> 00:32:10,295
We have newspaper people
on the payroll, don't we, Tom?

359
00:32:11,835 --> 00:32:13,962
They might like
a story like that.

360
00:32:14,071 --> 00:32:15,868
They might.
They just might.

361
00:32:19,410 --> 00:32:21,469
It's not personal, Sonny.

362
00:32:21,579 --> 00:32:22,978
It's strictly business.

363
00:32:26,083 --> 00:32:27,641
It's as cold as they come.

364
00:32:27,751 --> 00:32:31,312
Impossible to trace, so you don't
worry about prints, Mike.

365
00:32:31,422 --> 00:32:34,311
I put a special tape
on the trigger and the butt.

366
00:32:34,425 --> 00:32:35,824
Here. Try it.

367
00:32:47,605 --> 00:32:49,493
What's the matter,
the trigger too tight?

368
00:32:53,277 --> 00:32:55,336
- My ears.
- I left it noisy.

369
00:32:55,446 --> 00:33:00,179
That way it scares pain-in-the-ass
innocent bystanders away.

370
00:33:00,284 --> 00:33:02,514
All right, you shot them both.
Now what do you do?

371
00:33:05,389 --> 00:33:07,448
Sit down, finish my dinner.

372
00:33:07,558 --> 00:33:09,116
Come on, kid.
Don't fool around.

373
00:33:09,226 --> 00:33:12,787
Just let your hand drop to your side
and let the gun slip out.

374
00:33:12,896 --> 00:33:14,955
Everybody will still think
you got it.

375
00:33:15,065 --> 00:33:17,124
They're gonna be staring
at your face, Mike...

376
00:33:17,234 --> 00:33:20,294
so walk out of the place real fast,
but you don't run.

377
00:33:20,404 --> 00:33:23,794
Don't look nobody directly in the
eye, but don't look away, either.

378
00:33:23,907 --> 00:33:25,795
They're gonna be scared stiff
of you, believe me...

379
00:33:25,909 --> 00:33:27,274
so don't worry about nothing.

380
00:33:29,580 --> 00:33:31,309
You know, you're gonna turn out
all right.

381
00:33:31,415 --> 00:33:33,645
You take a long vacation,
nobody knows where...

382
00:33:33,751 --> 00:33:36,140
and we're gonna catch
the hell.

383
00:33:36,253 --> 00:33:38,312
How bad do you think
it's gonna be?

384
00:33:38,422 --> 00:33:40,310
Pretty goddamn bad.

385
00:33:40,424 --> 00:33:43,484
Probably all the other families
will line up against us.

386
00:33:43,594 --> 00:33:46,483
That's all right. These things
gotta happen every five years or so.

387
00:33:46,597 --> 00:33:49,157
Ten years.
Helps to get rid of the bad blood.

388
00:33:49,266 --> 00:33:51,826
Been ten years since
the last one.

389
00:33:51,935 --> 00:33:53,823
You gotta stop them
at the beginning...

390
00:33:53,937 --> 00:33:55,996
like they should have
stopped Hitler at Munich.

391
00:33:56,106 --> 00:33:57,994
They should have never let him
get away with that.

392
00:33:58,108 --> 00:33:59,905
They was just asking
for big trouble.

393
00:34:00,944 --> 00:34:03,504
You know, Mike,
we was all proud of you...

394
00:34:03,614 --> 00:34:05,275
being a hero and all.

395
00:34:05,382 --> 00:34:06,781
Your father too.

396
00:34:45,255 --> 00:34:46,984
Nothing.
Not a hint.

397
00:34:47,091 --> 00:34:48,490
Absolutely nothing.

398
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:52,649
Even Sollozzo's people don't know
where the meeting will be held.

399
00:34:53,931 --> 00:34:55,489
How much time do we have?

400
00:34:57,267 --> 00:34:58,996
Gonna pick you up in front
of Jack Dempsey's joint...

401
00:34:59,103 --> 00:35:01,492
in an hour and a half-
exactly an hour and a half.

402
00:35:03,273 --> 00:35:05,764
We could put a tail on them,
see how it turns out.

403
00:35:05,876 --> 00:35:09,107
Sollozzo'll lose our ass
going around the block.

404
00:35:09,213 --> 00:35:10,646
What about the negotiator?

405
00:35:10,748 --> 00:35:13,444
He's over at my place playing
pinochle with a couple of my men.

406
00:35:13,550 --> 00:35:15,245
He's happy.
They're letting him win.

407
00:35:15,352 --> 00:35:18,981
It's too much of a risk for Mike.
Maybe we ought to call it off.

408
00:35:19,089 --> 00:35:22,650
The negotiator keeps playing cards
until Mike's back safe and sound.

409
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:24,955
Why doesn't he blast who's ever
in the goddamn car?

410
00:35:25,062 --> 00:35:26,950
Too dangerous.
They'll be looking for that.

411
00:35:27,064 --> 00:35:29,123
Sollozzo might not
even be in the car, Sonny.

412
00:35:30,234 --> 00:35:31,633
I got it.

413
00:35:42,079 --> 00:35:43,478
Yeah.

414
00:35:56,927 --> 00:36:00,317
- Louis Restaurant in the Bronx.
- Is it reliable?

415
00:36:00,431 --> 00:36:02,160
That's my man
in McCluskey's precinct.

416
00:36:02,266 --> 00:36:05,099
A police captain's got to be
on call 24 hours a day.

417
00:36:05,202 --> 00:36:08,091
He signed out at that number
between 8:00 and 10:00.

418
00:36:08,205 --> 00:36:09,695
Anybody know this joint?

419
00:36:09,773 --> 00:36:13,163
Yeah, sure. I do.
It's perfect for us.

420
00:36:13,277 --> 00:36:15,438
A small family place,
good food.

421
00:36:15,546 --> 00:36:18,379
Everyone minds his business.
It's perfect.

422
00:36:18,482 --> 00:36:21,280
Pete, they got
an old-fashioned toilet-

423
00:36:21,385 --> 00:36:24,616
You know, the box
and the chain thing.

424
00:36:26,223 --> 00:36:28,783
We might be able
to tape the gun behind it.

425
00:36:28,892 --> 00:36:30,291
All right.

426
00:36:30,394 --> 00:36:33,557
Mike, you go to the restaurant.

427
00:36:33,664 --> 00:36:35,962
You eat, you talk for a while,
you relax.

428
00:36:36,066 --> 00:36:37,658
You make them relax.

429
00:36:37,768 --> 00:36:40,032
Then you get up
and go take a leak.

430
00:36:40,137 --> 00:36:42,799
No, better still,
you ask for permission to go.

431
00:36:42,906 --> 00:36:44,669
And when you come back,
you come out blasting.

432
00:36:44,775 --> 00:36:47,699
And don't take any chances.
Two shots in the head apiece.

433
00:36:47,811 --> 00:36:49,802
Now, listen.
I want somebody good-

434
00:36:49,913 --> 00:36:51,801
and I mean very good-
to plant that gun.

435
00:36:51,915 --> 00:36:54,907
I don't want him coming out
with just his dick in his hands.

436
00:36:55,018 --> 00:36:56,645
The gun will be there.

437
00:36:56,753 --> 00:37:00,985
All right, listen. You drive him
and you pick him up after the job.

438
00:37:01,091 --> 00:37:03,582
Come on. Let's move.

439
00:37:03,660 --> 00:37:05,059
Thank you, Tom.

440
00:37:08,432 --> 00:37:11,321
Did he tell you
to drop the gun right away?

441
00:37:11,435 --> 00:37:13,164
Yeah, a million times.

442
00:37:18,108 --> 00:37:20,497
Don't forget-
two shots apiece in the head...

443
00:37:20,611 --> 00:37:22,670
as soon as you
come out the door.

444
00:37:22,779 --> 00:37:24,178
Let's go.

445
00:37:28,785 --> 00:37:31,515
How long do you think it'll be
before I can come back?

446
00:37:33,457 --> 00:37:35,516
At least a year, Mike.

447
00:37:35,626 --> 00:37:39,187
Listen, I'll square with Mom you
not seeing her before you leave...

448
00:37:39,296 --> 00:37:43,687
and I'll get a message
to that girlfriend...

449
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,427
when I think the time is right.

450
00:37:51,475 --> 00:37:52,965
Take care.

451
00:37:56,146 --> 00:37:58,034
- See you, Mike.
- Okay, Tom.

452
00:38:30,447 --> 00:38:32,335
I'm glad you came, Mike.

453
00:38:32,449 --> 00:38:34,314
I hope we can
straighten everything out.

454
00:38:35,619 --> 00:38:38,474
This is terrible. It's not the way
I wanted things to go at all.

455
00:38:38,589 --> 00:38:40,352
It should have
never happened.

456
00:38:40,457 --> 00:38:42,516
I want to straighten
everything out tonight.

457
00:38:42,626 --> 00:38:45,015
I don't want my father
bothered anymore.

458
00:38:45,128 --> 00:38:49,189
He won't be, Mike.
I swear on my children he won't be.

459
00:38:49,299 --> 00:38:52,530
But you got to keep an open mind
when we talk.

460
00:38:52,636 --> 00:38:55,025
I hope you're not a hothead
like your brother Sonny.

461
00:38:55,138 --> 00:38:57,026
You can't talk business
with him.

462
00:38:58,809 --> 00:39:00,208
He's a good kid.

463
00:39:04,648 --> 00:39:06,809
I'm sorry about
the other night, Mike.

464
00:39:08,251 --> 00:39:10,640
I gotta frisk you,
so turn around, huh?

465
00:39:10,754 --> 00:39:12,483
